    "id": "cysts",
    "name": "Cysts",
    "category": "General & Energy",
    "emotionalRoot": "Running old painful mental movies over and over again. Nursing hurts and resentments, harboring a false growth of old sorrow, and refusing to let wounds heal because you use them to justify your defensive boundaries.",
    "metaphor": "Building fluid-filled capsule theaters in your tissues to keep playing your favorite tragic movies on loop, preserving your pain so you never have to move past it.",
    "physiologicalDescription": "Stress-induced chronic lymphatic congestion and local micro-vascular stagnation lead to the encapsulation of interstitial fluid, cellular debris, or sebum, forming localized cystic structures.",
    "sarcasticAdvice": "How lovely. Let's play the movie of how you were wronged in 2018 for the 5,000th time today. I'm sure your body absolutely loves growing little encapsulated fluid-filled monuments to your favorite historical grudges.",
    "mindfulnessPrompts": [
      "What old hurt or painful 'movie' am am I constantly running in my head, and how is my body literalizing it into a cyst?",
      "Am I ready to dissolve this capsule of old resentment and allow the emotional fluid to circulate and wash away?"
    ],
    "physicalTherapyTip": "Apply warm compresses to stimulate local circulation and lymph flow. Practice active lymphatic dry brushing or light drainage strokes from the periphery toward the heart, paired with mindfulness meditation focused on letting go.",
    "medical_safety": {
